metadata.name: The Storm ⛈ #89
metadata.description: Seemingly quiet amidst literary parlors and gilded seclusion, Emily Dickinson's life was likely at the mercy of a storm of emotions and feelings. In this work of generative art fully encoded in p5.js, the feelings of the people she lived with find an abstract representation, sometimes with fragments of her three her poems about storm.

metadata.name: Sandscapes #104
metadata.description:
Sandscapes generates multiple scenarios drawn with a random mix of colors with a noise reinterpretation.

Outputs are diverse with a common mist ambient, transporting the viewer to different environments such as sand dunes, red sunsets, purple sunrises, mountains, rivers, skin texture, or simply an elegant background with a unique mix of colors.

--
Sandscapes genera multiples escenarios dibujados con una mezcla aleatoria de colores y una reinterpretación con ruido.

Las imágenes son diversas con un ambiente de neblina común, y trasladan al espectador a diferentes entornos tales como dunas de arena, rojos atardeceres, violetas amaneceres, montañas, rios, textura de piel, o sencillamente un elegante background con una mezcla de colores única.

metadata.name: On the Road #32
metadata.description:
Adventure Road is printed and frozen with fading film slides from someone's archive.
The travel diary becomes an endless Möbius strip, spinning in circles like a wheel. How to stop coming back to it, rereading the notes in the margins of your life.

Aesthetically, I was inspired by Diango Hernández’s collage works and the book 'On the Road' by Jack Kerouac. This is a story about nomadism as lifestyle. 

Neural vintage photos are used as material for blobs. Exactly those, that are hardly distinguishable from each other, and which could be observed while driving a car along an endless highway.

Thanks to Yulikolay for helping with code, using p5.Riso.js library.
Source images are made with a help of DALL·E mini neural network.

metadata.name: Fragment #117
metadata.description:
▪️ 28 Variables
▪️ [left mouse button] hold to rotate
▪️ [mouse wheel] to zoom in and out
▪️ [right mouse button] to reset the view
▪️ [r] to toggle auto rotation [on by default]
▪️ [i] to toggle inverted colours
▪️ [s] to open the image capture popup on the top right [Live only capture]
▪️▪️ Maximum recommended width and height is 4096px [Higher resolutions might fail]
▪️ The piece does not stretch but instead it adjusts to the screen size and ratio
▪️ Designed to have a strong visual impact so might not be suitable for mobile
